The perils of reporting on an investigation of the president.

In the ‘Climate Fwd:’ Newsletter

A good reason to call your cable company.
President Trump

Trump Calls Border Talks a ‘Waste of Time’ and Dismisses Investigations

  • President Trump said in an exclusive interview with The Times that he will proceed on a border wall without lawmakers when talks end in two weeks.
  • In wide-ranging remarks, he also dismissed any suggestions of wrongdoing in the investigations that have ensnared his associates.

Mr. Trump wanted to talk. Here are five takeaways from what he said.

Mr. Trump’s campaign reported $19.2 million in cash on hand.

Extreme Weather

At Least 21 Believed Dead as Bitter Cold Spreads East

  • Temperatures remained near record lows in much of the region as parts of the Northeast also endured subzero wind chill readings.
  • Decades-old records fell. And, for one more day, even stepping outside remained a painful, risky experience.

University of Iowa Freshman Is Among the Dead After Deep Freeze

Gerald Belz, an 18-year-old who wanted to be a doctor, was found unconscious a short walk from his dorm. He had visited his parents just days before.

New York City’s homeless sought protection in transit stations and on trains.

U.S. Politics

Senate Rebukes Trump Over Troop Withdrawals From Syria and Afghanistan

  • The Senate, in a bipartisan rebuke to President Trump’s foreign policy, voted to advance a measure criticizing planned troop drawdowns.
  • The amendment was written by Senator Mitch McConnell of Kentucky and backed by virtually every Senate Republican.

Republicans Seize on Late-Term Abortion as a Potent 2020 Issue

After New York expanded abortion rights last week, anti-abortion advocates moved to halt similar legislative efforts, and to mobilize supporters ahead of the presidential race.

Senator Mitch McConnell called a proposal to make Election Day a holiday a “power grab” by Democrats.

The Global Economy

Friday’s Jobs Report Will Be a Mess. Here’s Why.

  • The monthlong government shutdown put an $11 billion dent in the economy, according to the Congressional Budget Office.
  • That damage could be all but invisible in Friday’s job figures, however. The timing could hardly be worse.

Here’s what the Fed’s halt on interest rates means for your wallet.

President Trump was optimistic about reaching a trade deal with China, but said he may leave some tariffs in place anyway.

Technology

Apple Shows Facebook Who Has the Power in an App Dispute

  • Apple shut down all of Facebook’s internal, custom-built iPhone apps after the tech giant broke its policies.
  • The iPhone maker controls the distribution of apps on its phones, demonstrating that even the world’s largest social network is beholden to the rules of others.

Tim Cook, Apple’s chief executive, could effectively become a technology regulator of last resort, our columnist writes.

SUPER BOWL LIII

Aaron Donald Doesn’t Look Like a Defensive Tackle. So He Reinvented the Position.

The speed and power of the Rams’ wrecking-ball lineman show that size isn’t everything in the N.F.L.

At 33, Sean McVay will be the youngest head coach in Super Bowl history. The league has noticed.

Can you balance the negative effects of football against support for your team? The Magazine’s ethics columnist weighs in.
